<h1>Elevation above pit</h1>

<p>
This tool will calcuate the elevation of each grid cell in a digital elevation model (DEM) above the nearest downslope pit cell or grid edge cell, depending on which is encountered first during the flow-path traverse. The resulting image is therefore a measure of relative landscape position. The user must specify the names of a <b><i>D8 flow pointer</i></b> grid, a DEM file, and the output file. The flow pointer grid must be derived using the <a href="FlowPointerD8.html">D8 flow algorithm</a>.</p>
<p><b><i>NoData</b></i> valued grid cells in the input pointer image will be assigned <b><i>NoData</b></i> values in the output image. The output raster is of the <i>float</i> data type and <i>continuous</i> data scale.</p>


